 to work on AA for criticals.  The way I see it is this:  Wizards are magical warriors.  We rely on our nukes/mana to keep us alive.  A Warrior rely's on their weapons.  I am not asking to critical as much as a warrior does with their weapons, just a little more often.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Balance Idea B:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Adjust Harvest either in mana percentage returned or in recast time.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Balance Idea C:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Increase the drop rate of a few notable spells...For example, Sunstrike.  A Kunark Spell which RARELY drops.  And there have been 2..going on 3, expansions since then.<br>
<br>
(All information was taken from <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com">eq.castersrealm.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for Wizards<br>
<br>
Level 60 Nukes[/u]<br>
<br>
*Sunstrike -  1615 DMG, 7 Second Cast Time, Instant Recast, Mana 450<br>
*Icy Spear of Solist - 1200 DMG, 3.5 Second Cast Time, 13 Second Recast, Mana 300<br>
*Lure of Ice - 825 DMG, 4.5 Second Cast Time, Instant Recast (&quot;Unrestistable&quot;...or supposed to be), Mana 320<br>
*Ancient: Destruction of Ice - 1200 DMG, 3.5 Second Cast Time, 13 Second Recast, Mana 250<br>
*Elnerick's Electrical Rending - 1890 DMG, 7.5 Second Cast Time, Instant Recast, Mana 525<br>
*Garrison's Superior Sundering - 2100 DMG, 8 Second Cast Time, Instant Recast, Mana 540<br>
*Porlos' Fury and Hsagras' Wrath - 2000 DMG, 6 Second Cast Time, 5 Second Recast, Mana 450 + 2 peridots..situational nuke<br>
<br>
************************************<br>
Criticals:  What can I say?  We need to critical a little more often than our current innate state.<br>
<br>
Spell Drop Rate/Location:  Most of these spells drop from mobs that most players will never get the chance to fight nor even see.  I personally will more than likely never see Garrison's Superior Sundering.  Perhaps Verant should re-evaluate either the location of spell drops or the frequency of them.<br>
<br>
Harvest:  Was great for the mana at level 34.  Currently when cast at level 56, I only see about a 7% Mana regain...Maybe less.  The 300 mana that you regain from harvest at level 60 is meaningless.  Either Harvest needs a massive revamp or an upgrade spell needs to be placed in game.  Harvest 2 =)<br>
<br>
****************************************<br>
<br>
I generally try to avoid these 'my class sucks' posts, but with all the balancing that Verant is trying to do, I don't see anything for wizards (or at least anything that I am aware of).<br>
<br>
Wizards need work.  Either in spell revamps, upgrade spells, or a change in spell drop rate...something must be done.<br>
<br>
/shrug....Just my 2 cents on the situation<br>
