<br>
A well-equiped pre-60 wizard is roughly 20% better now than before focus items/mage foci (mana reduction + damage increase) in DD damage over time.<br>
<br>
SoL with the increase in the number of FT items has helped the high end wizard's DPS significantly.<br>
<br>
Wizards compete with damage melee for raid and group spots.  While the focus items helped every casting class, it helped wizards against their main competition, hence they are improvements to the class.<br>
<br>
As for your improvements:<br>
<br>
Standard questions:<br>
<br>
1&gt; Will these fixes help wizards where they are weak?<br>
<br>
2&gt; Will it overpower them where they are strong?<br>
<br>
3&gt; Do these improvements scale with power level (ie, a 40-hour a week raiding guild player should be more powerful than a 5 hour a week player)?<br>
<br>
4&gt; What precicely does this do to wizard DPH in XP groups (AoE, ST-burn), quadding, single-mob burn soloing, and the like?<br>
<br>
5&gt; Should wizards outdamage warriors, monks or rogues in XP group settings over time?  Which should they outdamage?<br>
<br>
6&gt; What does this do to the wizards &quot;more uptime means less DPS&quot; problem (as compared to melee, whose DPS is constant with uptime)?  Is this a problem?<br>
<br>
7&gt; What does this do on raids?<br>
<br>
It is easy to make wizards more powerful.<br>
<br>
The hard part is figuring out what improvements are needed, justifying them, and then implementing it.<br>
